dcterms:description: miniImageNet is a benchmark dataset for few-shot learning, consisting of 60,000 images of size 84x84, divided into 64 training classes, 16 validation classes, and 20 test classes, with each class containing 600 images.
dcterms:title: miniImageNet

dcterms:description: CUB-200-2011 is a dataset consisting of 11,788 images of birds from 200 classes, with images resized to 84x84. It is commonly used for fine-grained image classification tasks.
dcterms:title: CUB-200-2011

dcterms:creator: Alex Krizhevsky

dcterms:description: CIFAR10 is a dataset containing 60,000 images across 10 classes, with each image sized at 32x32 pixels. It is widely used for benchmarking machine learning algorithms in image classification.
dcterms:title: CIFAR10

dcterms:creator: Alex Krizhevsky
Geoffrey Hinton
dcterms:description: CIFAR100 is similar to CIFAR10 but contains 60,000 images across 100 classes, with each image sized at 32x32 pixels. It is also used for benchmarking image classification algorithms.
dcterms:title: CIFAR100

dcterms:creator: Adam Coates

dcterms:description: STL-10 is a dataset containing 10 classes with 500 training images and 800 test images per class, with each image sized at 96x96 pixels. It is used for unsupervised feature learning and image classification.
dcterms:title: STL-10
